article.headline: Dayton 45, Urbana 7
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Kevin Hoyng tied a Dayton record with four touchdown passes as the Flyers routed Urbana 45-7 on Saturday. Hoyng, who completed 22-of-30 attempts, found Michael Jonard, Matt Champa and Justin Watkins for first-half scores, then hit Champa again for a TD in the third quarter. He finished with 285 yards passing. Backup quarterback Rob Florian was 11-of-13 with one touchdown to give the Flyers (2-0) a school-record 33 completions, breaking the mark of 29 set in 1974. Hoyng's TD total tied three other Dayton players who had thrown four TD passes in a game, including Kevin Johns, who did it twice in 1996. Urbana (1-1) scored its touchdown on C.J. Westler's 22-yard pass to Barry Quinn in the second quarter. Wrestler finished 12-of-22 with two interceptions.
